# Requirements
Download VS code and .Net SDK

## Project Selection
Run Command: "dotnet new" and see which app you want to create and choose appropriate application
In my case I created ASP.NET Core webapi application
For that you can run dotnet new webapi

## Add required packages
dotnet add package Microsoft.EntityFrameworkCore
dotnet add package Microsoft.EntityFrameworkCore.SQLServer
dotnet add package Microsoft.EntityFrameworkCore.Design

## For Entity Framework core
dotnet add package Microsoft.EntityFrameworkCore --version 7.0.0

## For SQLServer
dotnet add package Microsoft.EntityFrameworkCore.SQLServer --version 7.0.0

## For Authentication purposes
dotnet add package Microsoft.AspNetCore.Authentication.JwtBearer --version 7.0.1
dotnet add package Swashbuckle.AspNetCore.Filters

## AutoMapper
dotnet add package AutoMapper.Extensions.Microsoft.DependencyInjection

# Setup (SQL Server Management Studio)SSMS for Mac

1. Install Docker
2. Setup Docker Image Read Documentation(https://learn.microsoft.com/en-us/sql/linux/quickstart-install-connect-docker?view=sql-server-ver16&pivots=cs1-bash#pullandrun2022) 
For help you can also go this link and follow the instructions. (https://setapp.com/how-to/install-sql-server)


# For Migrations:
dotnet tool install --global dotnet-ef

For migration related things some commands are given below: 
For migration help: dotnet ef -h.
For adding migrations: dotnet ef migrations add InitialCreate
For running migrations: dotnet ef database update

# Run the Project on Mac
dotnet watch run

Goodluck!!! Hurray :)